  9  /-! # Filter bases
 10  
 11  In this file we define `filter.has_basis l p s`, where `l` is a filter on `α`, `p` is a predicate
 12  on some index set `ι`, and `s : ι → set α`.
 13  
 14  ## Main statements
 15  
 16  * `has_basis.mem_iff`, `has_basis.mem_of_superset`, `has_basis.mem_of_mem` : restate `t ∈ f` in terms
 17    of a basis;
 18  * `basis_sets` : all sets of a filter form a basis;
 19  * `has_basis.inf`, `has_basis.inf_principal`, `has_basis.prod`, `has_basis.prod_self`,
 20    `has_basis.map`, `has_basis.comap` : combinators to construct filters of `l ⊓ l'`,
 21    `l ⊓ principal t`, `l.prod l'`, `l.prod l`, `l.map f`, `l.comap f` respectively;
 22  * `has_basis.le_iff`, `has_basis.ge_iff`, has_basis.le_basis_iff` : restate `l ≤ l'` in terms
 23    of bases.
 24  * `has_basis.tendsto_right_iff`, `has_basis.tendsto_left_iff`, `has_basis.tendsto_iff` : restate
 25    `tendsto f l l'` in terms of bases.
 26  
 27  ## Implementation notes
 28  
 29  As with `Union`/`bUnion`/`sUnion`, there are three different approaches to filter bases:
 30  
 31  * `has_basis l s`, `s : set (set α)`;
 32  * `has_basis l s`, `s : ι → set α`;
 33  * `has_basis l p s`, `p : ι → Prop`, `s : ι → set α`.
 34  
 35  We use the latter one because, e.g., `𝓝 x` in an `emetric_space` or in a `metric_space` has a basis
 36  of this form. The other two can be emulated using `s = id` or `p = λ _, true`.
 37  
 38  With this approach sometimes one needs to `simp` the statement provided by the `has_basis`
 39  machinery, e.g., `simp only [exists_prop, true_and]` or `simp only [forall_const]` can help
 40  with the case `p = λ _, true`.
 41  -/
 42  
 43  namespace filter
 44  variables {α : Type*} {β : Type*} {γ : Type*} {ι : Type*} {ι' : Type*}
id                                                 ┴
typ                                                ┴

 48  /-- We say that a filter `l` has a basis `s : ι → set α` bounded by `p : ι → Prop`,
 49  if `t ∈ l` if and only if `t` includes `s i` for some `i` such that `p i`. -/
 50  protected def has_basis (l : filter α) (p : ι → Prop) (s : ι → set α) : Prop :=
